Program Description:
This program creates seven POSIX threads. Each thread acts as a chat bot
that writes a quote to a shared file named QUOTE.txt. The program uses a
POSIX semaphore named FLAG to control access to the shared file so that
only one thread writes to the file at a time.

When the program starts, it creates QUOTE.txt and writes the process ID
to the file. Then it creates seven threads. Even-numbered threads write
the Brian Kernighan quote every two seconds, and odd-numbered threads
write the Edsger Dijkstra quote every three seconds. Each thread writes
to the file eight total times.

Build Instructions:
To compile the program, run:

make

Run Instructions:
To run the program, run:

./bots

Output:
The program creates a file named QUOTE.txt in the current directory.
QUOTE.txt begins with the process ID of the running program, followed by
the thread IDs and assigned quotes written by the seven threads.

Clean Instructions:
To remove object files, the executable, and QUOTE.txt, run:

make clean

Notes:
The executable is named bots.
The program uses pthread_create(), pthread_join(), sem_init(),
sem_wait(), sem_post(), and sem_destroy().
The system() function is not used.